properties.occurrenceRemarks: I saw a female Hawaiian Monk Seal and a pup. A "Pup-sitter" from The Marine Mammal Center’s Ke Kai Ola group told me that the pup was a two week old male. This was the mother's second pup. I observed the pup barking, moving from the ocean to the beach and trying to suckle on its mother. Volunteers said the mother had already given it swimming lessons. It was surfing the waves and exploring. I also saw a male seal, who was believed to be a relative, watching the mother and pup for a few minutes from the ocean. Less than two weeks later, the mother lost her pup. In December I asked the staff of The Marine Mammal Center about the cause of death and I was told that it was still under investigation. To see video of the seals, go to: http://www.bigislandvideonews.com/2015/12/20/video-hawaiian-monk-seal-at-keokea-loses-2nd-pup/
